# Backend schema to frontend sync

When a backend API schema, request/response contract, route, or status code changes, update frontend calls for that same endpoint in the same task.

## Required updates

- Regenerate or update typed API clients/types derived from backend OpenAPI/contracts.
- Update frontend request payloads, query params, headers, and response handling to match the new schema.
- Update endpoint paths/method usage where renamed, moved, or deprecated.
- Remove or migrate frontend code that depends on removed fields or old response shapes.

## Verification before completion

- Confirm frontend compiles/types check after schema-driven changes.
- Update or add tests covering the changed endpoint contract (backend and frontend where applicable).
- Do not mark work complete while backend schema and frontend endpoint usage are out of sync.
